Privacy Policy
At SquadApp, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your data when you use our mobile application and website. By accessing or using SquadApp, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.
Information Collection
We may collect personal information from users in various ways, including when you register, create an account, or use our services. This information may include your name, email, and other details. Additionally, we may gather certain information automatically, such as IP addresses, device information, usage patterns, and cookies to enhance user experience and improve our services.
Use of Information
We use the collected information to personalize user experience, improve our app and website, communicate with users regarding updates, offers, and important information related to SquadApp, and to comply with legal obligations. The data also helps us analyze user behavior and preferences to enhance our services.
Data Sharing
We do not sell, trade, or rent users' personal information to third parties. However, we may share aggregated demographic information not linked to any personal identification with our partners, advertisers, or affiliates for marketing and analytical purposes.
Data Security
We prioritize the security of your personal information and employ appropriate data collection, storage, and processing practices to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of your data stored on our app and website.
Children's Privacy
Although SquadApp is designed to be suitable for users of all ages, we prioritize the safety and privacy of our users. We do not knowingly collect personal information from individuals under the age of 13. If you are a parent or guardian and have reason to believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please reach out to us immediately so that we can promptly address and remove such information from our records.
Changes to Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. We encourage users to frequently check this page for any changes to stay informed about how we are protecting the personal information we collect. You acknowledge and agree that it is your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy periodically.